9_21	0.3076923076923077	If spending were to increase just enough to keep up with inflation from now through 2009, the report concluded, it would use $595 billion of the $996 billion surplus.
9_22	0.2	The Democrats then looked at emergency spending, money that Congress appropriates each year to deal with unanticipated needs ranging from hurricanes to aid for farmers.
